
### Feature Description

Livestock farming plays a crucial role in both food production and renewable energy generation. Biogas, produced from livestock waste, is a renewable energy source that can significantly contribute to sustainable energy goals. This project aims to leverage machine learning to predict biogas production from various livestock types, including cattle, dairy cows, poultry, and swine. By analyzing historical data and various influencing factors, the project seeks to provide valuable insights that can optimize farming practices, guide investment decisions, and support sustainable energy initiatives.
